{
  "texts": [
    "It is the eagerness or readiness to exert effort towards achieving objectives.",
    "Motivation in learning can originate from curiosity, interest in the subject matter, or the pleasure of mastering a new skill (Mamlok-Naaman, 2011).",
    "These elements work together in a dynamic system to facilitate self-regulated learning.",
    "This process enables learners to take an active role in their learning, using strategies to acquire, comprehend, and remember information, as well as to evaluate and adjust their learning approaches as needed.",
    "A crucial component to support SRL strategies among learners is formative feedback (Nicol & Macfarlane-Dick, 2006)."
  ]
}